The paper deals with image reconstruction and interpolation using electron tomography, which is a common application in computer vision (CV). The use of regularization techniques and denoising algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to the information theory (IT) sub-category. The use of modern algorithms and mathematical conditions for convergence suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (MM) sub-category. The use of sparse sampling and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to the data structures (DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of numerical analysis and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to the numerical analysis (NA) sub-category.
